obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32167)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32167&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called ^1[the Deposit Insurance and`
  line `Credit Guarantee Corporation] Act, 1961.`
  line
  line `(2) It extend to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "the Deposit Insurance Corporation" (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. 1st January, 1962, vide notification No. G.S.R. 18, dated 28th December, 1961, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32168)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32168&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) banking means the accepting for the purpose of lending or investment, of deposits of money`
  line `from the public repayable on demand or otherwise, and withdrawable by cheque, draft, order or`
  line otherwise;
  line
  line `(b) banking company means any company which transacts the business of banking in India and`
  line `includes the State Bank ^1[and a subsidiary bank], but does not include the ^2[Tamil Nadu Industrial`
  line `Investment Corporation Limited].`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Any company which is engaged in the manufacture of goods or carries on any`
  line `trade and which accepts deposits of money from the public merely for the purpose of financing its`
  line `business as such manufacturer or trader shall not be deemed to transact the business of banking`
  line `within the meaning of this clause;`
  line
  line `(c) Board means the Board of directors constituted under section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) company means any company as defined in section 3 of the Companies Act, (1 of 1956) and`
  line `includes a foreign company within the meaning of section 591 of that Act;`
  line
  line `^3[(dd) co-operative bank means a State co-operative bank, a Central co-operative bank and a`
  line `primary co-operative bank;]`
  line
  line `(e) Corporation means ^4[the Deposit Insurance and Credit Guarantee Corporation] established`
  line `under section 3;`
  line
  line `^5[(ee) corresponding new bank means a corresponding new bank constituted under section 3 of`
  line `the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) or, as the`
  line `case may be, under section 3 of the Banking companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)`
  line `Act, 1980 (40 of 1980);]`
  line
  line `^6[(eea) credit institution means all or any of the following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a banking company;`
  line
  line `(ii) a corresponding new bank;`
  line
  line `(iii) a Regional Rural Bank;`
  line
  line `(iv) a co-operative bank;`
  line
  line `(v) a financial institution];`
  line
  line `(f) defunct banking company means a banking company--`
  line
  line `(i) which has been prohibited from receiving fresh deposits; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which has been ordered to be wound up; or`
  line
  line `(iii) which has transferred all its deposit liabilities in India to any other institution; or`
  line
  line `(iv) which has ceased to be a banking company within the meaning of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 36A of ^7[the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)], or has converted itself into a`
  line `non-banking company; or`
  line
  line `(v) in respect of which a liquidator has been appointed in pursuance of a resolution for the`
  line `voluntary winding up of its affairs; or`
  line
  line `(vi) in respect of which any scheme of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction has`
  line `been sanctioned by any competent authority and the said scheme does not permit the acceptance of`
  line `fresh deposits; or`
  line
  line `(vii) which has been granted a moratorium which is in operation; or`
  line
  line `(viii) in respect of which an application for the winding up of its affairs is pending in a`
  line `^8[competent Court; or]`
  line
  line `^9[(ix) in respect of which any direction, prohibition, order or scheme referred to in sub-section (1) of section 18A is issued or made;]`
  line
  line `^10[(ff) defunct co-operative bank means a co-operative bank--`
  line
  line `(i) which has been prohibited from receiving fresh deposits; or`
  line
  line `(ii) which has been ordered or directed to be wound up; or`
  line
  line `(iii) which has transferred all its deposit liabilities in India to any other institution; or`
  line
  line `(iv) which has ceased to be a co-operative bank within the meaning of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 36A of the Banking Regulation Act 1949 (10 of 1949); or`
  line
  line `(v) which has converted itself into a non-banking co-operative society; or`
  line
  line `(vi) in respect of which any scheme of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction has`
  line `been sanctioned under any law for the time being in force and such scheme does not permit the`
  line `acceptance of fresh deposits; or`
  line
  line `(vii) which has been granted a moratorium which is in operation; or`
  line
  line `(viii) in respect of which an application for winding up is pending before the Registrar of`
  line `Co-operative Societies or other competent authority under any law relating to co-operative`
  line `societies for the time being in force ^11[in a State;or]`
  line
  line `^12[(ix) in respect of which any direction, prohibition, order or scheme referred to in sub-section (1) of section 18-A is issued or made;]`
  line
  line `(g) “deposit means the aggregate of the unpaid balances due to a depositor (other than a foreign`
  line `Government, the Central Government, a State Government ^13[ ^14[ a corresponding new bank or`
  line `^15[a Regional Rural Bank or a banking company]] or a co-operative bank]) in respect of all his`
  line `accounts by whatever name called, ^16[ ^17[ with a corresponding new bank or ^18[with a Regional Rural`
  line `Bank or with a banking company]] or a co-operative bank] and includes credit balances in any cash`
  line `credit account but does not include,--`
  line
  line `(i) where ^15[a Regional Rural Bank or a banking company or a co-operative bank] at the`
  line `commencement of this Act ^19[or where an eligible co-operative bank at the commencement of the`
  line `Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1968 (56 of 1968)] is working under a scheme`
  line `of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction sanctioned by any competent authority`
  line `providing for the acceptance of fresh deposits any amount due to the depositor in respect of his`
  line `deposit before the date of the coming into force of the scheme of the extent it is not credited after`
  line `to the said date under the provisions of that scheme; or`
  line
  line `^20[(ia) any amount due on account of any deposit with any insured bank which has been`
  line `specially exempted in this behalf by the Corporation with the previous approval of the Reserve`
  line `Bank; or]`
  line
  line `(ii) any amount due on account of any deposit received outside India;`
  line
  line `^19[(gg) eligible co-operative bank means a co-operative bank the law for the time being`
  line `governing which provides that--`
  line
  line `(i) an order for the winding up, or an order sanctioning a scheme of compromise or`
  line `arrangement or of amalgamation or reconstruction, of the bank may be made only with the`
  line `previous sanction in writing of the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(ii) an order for the winding up of the bank shall be made if so required by the Reserve Bank`
  line `in the circumstances referred to in section 13D;`
  line
  line `(iii) if so required by the Reserve bank in public interest or for preventing the affairs of the`
  line `bank being conducted in a manner detrimental to the interests of the depositors or for securing the`
  line `proper management of the bank, an order shall be made for the supersession of the committee of`
  line `management or other managing body (by whatever name called) of the bank and the appointment`
  line `of an administrator therefor for such period or periods not exceeding 5 years in the aggregate as`
  line `may from time to time be specified by the Reserve Bank;`
  line
  line `(iv) an order for the winding up of the bank or an order sanctioning a scheme of compromise`
  line `or arrangement or of amalgamation or reconstruction or an order for the supersession of the`
  line `committee of management or other managing body (by whatever name called) of the bank and`
  line `the appointment of an administrator therefor made with the previous sanction in writing or on the`
  line `requisition of the Reserve Bank shall not be liable to be called in question in any manner; and`
  line
  line `(v) the liquidator or the insured bank or the transferee bank, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `under an obligation to repay the Corporation in the circumstances to the extent and in the manner`
  line `referred to in section 21;]`
  line
  line `(h) existing banking company means a banking company carrying on the business of banking at`
  line `the commencement of this Act which either holds a licence at such commencement under section 22`
  line `of ^21[the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)] or having applied for such licence has not been`
  line
  line `informed by notice in writing by the Reserve Bank that a licence cannot be granted to it and includes`
  line `the State Bank and subsidiary bank, but does not include a defunct banking company;`
  line
  line `^22[(hh) existing co-operative bank means a co-operative bank carrying on the business of`
  line `banking at the commencement of the Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1968`
  line `(56 of 1968), which either holds a licence at such commencement under section 22 of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), or having applied for such licence has not been informed by`
  line `notice in writing by the Reserve Bank that a licence cannot be granted to it but does not include a`
  line `defunct co-operative bank;]`
  line
  line `^23[(hha) Financial institution means any financial institution within the meaning of clause (c) of`
  line `section 451 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934);]`
  line
  line `^24[(i) insured bank means ^25[a banking company],`
  line `^26[or a Regional Rural Bank]]`
  line `^27[or a`
  line `corresponding new bank] or an eligible co-operative bank for the time being registered under the`
  line `provisions of this Act and includes for the purposes of sections 16, 17, 18 and 21,--`
  line
  line `^28[(i) a banking company referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13, or`
  line
  line `(ia) a corresponding new bank to which the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13 apply, or]`
  line
  line `(ii) a co-operative bank referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) of section 13C,]`
  line
  line `the registration whereof has been cancelled under section 13, or, as the case may be, under section`
  line 13C;]
  line
  line `(j)insured deposit means the deposit or any portion thereof the repayment whereof is insured by`
  line `the Corporation under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) new banking company means a banking company which begins to transact the business of`
  line `banking after the commencement of this Act under a licence granted to it under section 22 ^29[the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)] ^30***;`
  line
  line `^22[(kk)] new co-operative bank means a co-operative bank which begins to transact the business`
  line `of banking after the commencement of the Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1968`
  line `(56 of 1968), under a licence granted to it under section 22 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949`
  line `(10 of 1949), and includes a primary credit society becoming a primary co-operative bank after such`
  line commencement;]
  line
  line `(l) premium means the sum payable by an insured bank under section 15 of this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) prescribed means prescribed by regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^27[(ma) Regional Rural Bank means a Regional Rural Bank established under section 3 of the`
  line `Regional Rural Banks Act, 1976 (21 of 1976);]`
  line
  line `(n) Reserve Bank means the Reserve Bank of India constituted under the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `Act, 1934 ( 2 of 1934);`
  line
  line `(o) State Bank means the State Bank of India constituted under the State Bank of India Act,`
  line `1955 (23 of 1955);`
  line
  line `(p)subsidiary bank shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 2 of the State Bank of India`
  line `(Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959);`
  line
  line `^31[(q) the expressions central co-operative bank, ^32*** and State Co-operative Bank shall have`
  line `the meanings respectively assigned to them in the National Bank for Agriculture and Rural`
  line `Development Act, 1981 (61 of 1981);`
  line
  line `(r) the expressions ^33[co-operative society, primary co-operative bank] and primary credit`
  line `society shall have the meanings respectively, assigned to them in Part V of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)].`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 56, for , a subsidiary bank and any other banking institution notified under section 51 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 1974, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for Madras Industrial Investment Corporation Limited (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 56, for sub-clause (ee) (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s.2, for the Banking companies Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 30 of 2021, s. 2, for “competent Court” (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 30 of 2021, s. 2, for “in a State.” (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).1`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s.3, for or a banking company (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 5 of 1970, s. 20, for , a banking company (w.e.f. 19-7-1969).`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 21 of 1976, s. 33, for a banking company (w.e.f. 26-9-1975).`
  line
  line `16. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 3, for with a banking company (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by Act 5 of 1970, s. 20, for with a banking company (w.e.f. 19-7-1969).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by Act 21 of 1976, s. 33, for with a baking company (w.e.f. 26-9-1975).`
  line
  line `19. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `20. Ins. by Act 81 of 1985, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
  line
  line `21. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 2, for the Banking Companies Act, 1949 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `22. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `23. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `24. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 3, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `25. Subs. by Act 19 of 1988, s. 3 and Second Schedule, for corresponding new bank or a banking company (w.e.f. 31-3-1988).`
  line
  line `26. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `27. Ins. by Act 21 of 1976, s. 33 (w.e.f. 26-9-1975).`
  line
  line `28. Subs. by s. 56, ibid., for, sub-clause (i) (w.e.f. 19-7-1969).`
  line
  line `29. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 2, for the Banking Companies Act, 1949 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `30.The words and figures , and includes any banking institution notified under section 51 of the said Act after such commencement omitted by Act 1 of 1984, s. 56 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
