obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32169)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment and incorporation of Deposit Insurance Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32169&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, establish a Corporation by the name of the`
  line `Deposit Insurance Corporation which shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold or dispose of property and`
  line `to contract, and may, by the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `^1[1A) Any reference in this Act to the Deposit Insurance Corporation shall, on and from the date on`
  line `which Chapter II of the Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment and Miscellaneous Provisions) Act,`
  line `1978 (21 of 1978), comes into force, be construed as a reference to the Deposit Insurance and Credit`
  line `Guarantee Corporation.]`
  line
  line `(2) The head office of the Corporation shall be at Bombay, but it may, with the previous sanction of`
  line `the Reserve Bank, establish branches or agencies in any other place in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32170)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Capital of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32170&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Capital of Corporation.--(1) The authorised capital of the Corporation shall be one crore of`
  line `rupees but the Central Government may, in consultation with the Reserve Bank, increase such capital`
  line `from time to time, so, however, that the total authorised capital shall not exceed`
  line `^2[fifty crores of rupees].`
  line
  line `(2) The ^3[issued capital] for the time being of the Corporation shall be fully paid-up and shall stand`
  line `allotted to the Reserve Bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 4, for section 4 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 57, for "fifteen crores" (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8, for "authorised capital" (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32171)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Management of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32171&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The general superintendence, direction and the management of`
  line `the affairs and business of the Corporation shall vest in a Board of directors which may exercise all`
  line `powers and do all acts and things which may be exercised or done by the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32172)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Board of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32172&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board of directors of the Corporation shall consist of the following,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the Governor, for the time being, of the Reserve Bank or, if the Reserve Bank, in pursuance`
  line `of the decision of the Committee of the Central Board of Directors of that Bank, nominates any`
  line `Deputy Governor for the purpose, the Deputy Governor so nominated, who shall be the Chairman of`
  line `the Board;]`
  line
  line `(b)`
  line `^2[a Deputy Governor or any other officer] of the Reserve Bank nominated by that bank;`
  line
  line `(c) an officer of the Central Government nominated by that Government;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) five directors nominated by the Central Government in consultation with the Reserve Bank,`
  line `three of whom shall be persons having special knowledge of commercial banking, insurance,`
  line `commerce, industry or finance and two of whom shall be persons having special knowledge of, or`
  line `experience in, co-operative banking or co-operative movement and none of the directors shall be an`
  line `officer of Government or of the Reserve Bank or an officer or other employee of the Corporation or a`
  line `director, an officer or other employee of a banking company or a co-operative bank or otherwise`
  line `actively connected with a banking company or a co-operative bank].`
  line
  line `^4[(e) four directors, nominated by the Central Government in consultation with the Reserve Bank,`
  line `having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of accountancy, agriculture and rural`
  line `economy, banking, co-operation, economics, finance, law or small-scale industry or any other matter,`
  line `the special knowledge of, and practical experience in which, is likely, in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government to be useful to the Corporation.]`
  line
  line `^5[(2)(i). A director nominated under clause (b) or clause (c)`
  line `^6[or clause (d) or clause (e)] of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall hold office during the pleasure of the authority nominating him; and`
  line
  line `^7[(ii) Subject to the provisions contained in clause (i), a director nominated under clause (d) or`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (1), shall hold office for such period, not exceeding three years, as may be`
  line `specified by the Central Government in this behalf, ^8*** and shall be eligible for re-nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such director shall hold office continuously for a period exceeding six years.]]`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be capable of being nominated as a director under clause (d)`
  line `^9[or clause (e)] of`
  line `sub-section (1) if--`
  line
  line `(a) he has been removed or dismissed from the service of Government or of a local authority or of`
  line `a corporation or company in which not less than fifty-one per cent. of the paid-up share capital is held`
  line `by Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) he is or at any time has been adjudicated as insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts`
  line `or has compounded with his creditors; or`
  line
  line `(c) he is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent Court; or`
  line
  line `(d) he has been convicted of any offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government,`
  line `involves moral turpitude.`
  line
  line `(4) If a director nominated under clause (d) of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in clauses (a) to (d) of`
  line `sub-section (3); or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the Board for more than three consecutive meetings thereof; or`
  line
  line `(c) becomes a director or an officer or an employee of an insured bank or is, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, otherwise actively connected with such bank; or`
  line
  line `(d) becomes an officer or other employee of Government or of the Reserve Bank or of the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `^10[(5) If a director nominated under clause (e) of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) becomes subject to any of the disqualifications mentioned in clauses (a) to (d) of`
  line `sub-section (3); or`
  line
  line `(b) is absent without leave of the Board for more than three consecutive meetings thereof,`
  line
  line `his seat shall thereupon becomes vacant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for clause (a) (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 5, for "a Deputy Governor" (w.e.f. 7-5-1970).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 5, for clause (d) (w.e.f. 10-3-1986).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 58, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 24 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `8. The words "and thereafter until his successor assumes office" omitted by Act 45 of 2006, s. 17 (w.e.f. 16-10-2006).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 58 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 58 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32173)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32173&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall meet at such times and places and shall observe such`
  line `rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman or, if for any reason he is unable to attend the director nominated under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 6 shall preside at meetings of the Board and, in the event of equality of votes,`
  line `shall have a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32174)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Committees of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32174&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may constitute an Executive Committee consisting`
  line `of such number of directors as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall discharge such functions as may be prescribed or may be`
  line `delegated to it by the Board.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may constitute such other committees, whether consisting wholly of directors or`
  line `wholly of other persons or partly of directors and partly of other persons as it thinks fit for the purpose of`
  line `discharging such of its functions as may be prescribed or may be delegated to them by the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) A committee constituted under this section shall meet at such times and places and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The members of a committee (other than directors of the Board) shall be paid by the Corporation`
  line `such fees and allowances for attending its meetings and for attending to any other work of the`
  line `Corporation as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32175)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Fees and allowances of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32175&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The directors of the Board shall be paid by the Corporation`
  line `such fees and allowances for attending the meetings of the Board or of any its committees and for`
  line `attending to any other work of the Corporation as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no fees shall be payable to the Chairman or to the director nominated under clause (b)`
  line `of clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (32176)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Registration of existing banking companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32176&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[10. Registration of existing banking companies.--The Corporation shall register every existing`
  line `banking company as an insured bank before the expiry of thirty days from the date of commencement of`
  line `this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32177)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Registration of new banking companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32177&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall register every new banking`
  line `company as an insured bank as soon as may be after it is granted a licence under section 22 of the`
  line `^1[Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)], ^2***`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Banking Companies Act, 1949" (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures ", or, as the case may be, after it is notified under section 51 of the said Act" omitted by Act 1 of 1984,`
  line `s. 59 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (32178)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 12
  title `Registration of Regional Rural Banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1976, s. 33 (w.e.f. 26-9-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32178&sectionno=11A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Registration of Regional Rural Banks.--The Corporation shall register every Regional`
  line `Rural Bank, before the expiry of thirty days from the date of its establishment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32179)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Registration of defunct banking companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32179&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Every banking company being a defunct banking`
  line `company at the commencement of this Act, by reason of sub-clause (vii) or sub-clause (viii) of clause (f) of section 2 shall, unless it becomes a defunct banking company under any other sub-clause of that clause,`
  line `be registered by the Corporation as an insured bank as soon as may be after the termination of the order`
  line `moratorium or, as the case may be, the rejection of the application for its winding up.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32180)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Cancellation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32180&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The registration of a banking company as an insured bank`
  line `shall stand cancelled on the occurrence of any of the following events, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if it has been prohibited from receiving fresh deposits; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it has been informed by notice in writing by the Reserve Bank that its licence has been`
  line `cancelled under section 22 of ^2[the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)] or that a licence`
  line `under that section cannot be granted to it; or`
  line
  line `(c) if it has been ordered to be wound up; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it has transferred all its deposit liabilities in India to any other institution; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it has ceased to be a banking company within the meaning of sub-section (2) of section 36A`
  line `of ^2[the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)] or has converted itself into a non-banking`
  line `company; or`
  line
  line `(f) if a liquidator has been appointed in pursuance of a resolution for the voluntary winding up of`
  line `its affairs; or`
  line
  line `(g) if in respect of it any scheme of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction has been`
  line `sanctioned by any competent authority and the said scheme does not permit the acceptance of fresh`
  line `deposits; or`
  line
  line `(h) if it has amalgamated with any other banking institution.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) The provisions of clauses (a), ^4*** (c), (d) and (h) of sub-section (1) shall apply to a`
  line `corresponding new bank as they apply to a banking company.]`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The provisions of clauses (a), ^4 *** (c), (d) and (h) of sub-section (1) shall apply to a Regional`
  line `Rural Bank as they apply to a banking company.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 13 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 5 of 1970, s. 20 (w.e.f. 19-7-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 2, for "the Banking Companies Act, 1949" (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 5 of 1970, s. 20 (w.e.f. 19-7-1969).`
  line
  line `4. The brackets and letter "(b)," omitted by 1 of 1984, s. 60 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 21 of 1976, s. 33 (w.e.f. 26-9-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (32181)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 15
  title `Registration of co-operative banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32181&sectionno=13A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Registration of co-operative banks.--(1) No co-operative bank shall be registered under this`
  line `section unless it is an eligible co-operative bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject as aforesaid--`
  line
  line `(a) the Corporation shall register every existing co-operative bank as an insured bank before the`
  line `expiry of thirty days next following the commencement of the Deposit Insurance Corporation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1968 (56 of 1968);`
  line
  line `(b) the Corporation shall register as an insured bank--`
  line
  line `(i) every new co-operative bank [other than a primary credit society becoming a primary`
  line `co-operative bank after the commencement of the Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1968 (56 of 1968)] as soon as may be after it is granted a licence under section 22 of the`
  line `Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(ii) a primary credit society becoming a primary co-operative bank after such commencement`
  line `within three months of its having made an application for a licence under the said section:`
  line
  line `Provided that a bank referred to in clause (b) shall not be so registered if it has been informed by`
  line `notice in writing by the Reserve Bank that such a licence cannot be granted to it.`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) every co-operative bank which has come into existence after the commencement of the`
  line `Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1968 (56 of 1968), as a result of the division of any other co-operative society carrying on business as a co-operative bank, or the amalgamation`
  line `of two or more co-operative societies carrying on banking business, at the commencement of the`
  line `Banking Laws (Application to Co-operative Societies) Act, 1965 (23 of 1965), or at any time`
  line `thereafter, within three months of its having made an application for a licence under the said`
  line section;]]
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 61 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b:
  sectionId (32182)
  sectionNo 13B
  orderNo 16
  title `Registration of defunct co-operative banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32182&sectionno=13B&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[13B. Registration of defunct co-operative banks.--Every co-operative bank being a defunct`
  line `co-operative bank at the commencement of the Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment) Act, 1968`
  line `(56 of 1968), by reason of sub-clause (vii) or Sub-clause (viii) of clause (ff) of section 2 shall, unless it`
  line `becomes a defunct co-operative bank under any other sub-clause of that clause, be registered by the`
  line `Corporation as an insured bank as soon as may be after the termination of the order of moratorium, or as`
  line `the case may be, the rejection or dismissal of the application for its winding up provided it is an eligible`
  line `co-operative bank and it either holds a licence granted under section 22 of the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), or having applied for such licence in accordance with that section, has not been`
  line `informed by notice in writing by the Reserve Bank that a licence cannot be granted to it.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_c:
  sectionId (32183)
  sectionNo 13C
  orderNo 17
  title `Cancellation of registration of co-operative banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32183&sectionno=13C&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[13C. Cancellation of registration of co-operative banks.--The registration of a co-operative bank`
  line `as an insured bank shall stand cancelled on the occurrence of any of the following events, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) if it has been prohibited from accepting fresh deposits; or`
  line
  line `(b) if it has been informed by notice in writing by the Reserve Bank that its licence has been`
  line `cancelled under section 22 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), or a licence under that`
  line `section cannot be granted to it; or`
  line
  line `(c) if it has been ordered or directed to be wound up; or`
  line
  line `(d) if it has transferred all its deposit liabilities in India to any other institution; or`
  line
  line `(e) if it has ceased to be a co-operative bank within the meaning of sub-section (2) of section 36A`
  line `of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949); or`
  line
  line `(f) if it has converted itself into a non-banking co-operative society; or`
  line
  line `(g) if in respect of it any scheme of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction has been`
  line `sanctioned by a competent authority and the said scheme does not permit the acceptance by it of fresh`
  line `deposits; or`
  line
  line `(h) if it has been amalgamated with any other co-operative society; or`
  line
  line `(i) if it ceases to be an eligible co-operative bank, that is, if the law for the time being governing`
  line `such co-operative bank does not provide for all or any of the matters referred to in clause (gg) of`
  line `section 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_d:
  sectionId (32184)
  sectionNo 13D
  orderNo 18
  title `Circumstances in which Reserve Bank may require winding up of co-operative banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32184&sectionno=13D&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_13_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[13D. Circumstances in which Reserve Bank may require winding up of co-operative`
  line `banks.--(1) The circumstances referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (gg) of section 2 (being`
  line `circumstances in which the Reserve Bank may require the winding up of a co-operative bank) are the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the co-operative bank has failed to comply with the requirements specified in section 11`
  line `of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949); or`
  line
  line `(b) that the co-operative bank has by reason of the provisions of section 22 of the said Act`
  line `become disentitled to carry on banking business in India; or`
  line
  line `(c) that the co-operative bank has been prohibited from receiving fresh deposits by an order under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 35 of the said Act or under clause (b) of sub-section (3A) of section 42 of`
  line `the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); or`
  line
  line `(d) that the co-operative bank having failed to comply with any requirement of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), other than the requirements laid down in section 11 thereof, has`
  line
  line `continued such failure or, having contravened any provision of that Act has continued such`
  line `contravention beyond such period or periods as may be specified in that behalf by the Reserve Bank`
  line `from time to time, after notice in writing of such failure or contravention has been conveyed to the`
  line `co-operative bank; or`
  line
  line `(e) that the co-operative bank is unable to pay its debts; or`
  line
  line `(f) that in the opinion of the Reserve Bank--`
  line
  line `(i) a compromise or arrangement sanctioned by a competent authority in respect of the`
  line `co-operative bank cannot be worked satisfactorily with or without modifications, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the continuance of the co-operative bank is prejudicial to the interests of its depositors.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of any other law for the time being in force, a co-operative`
  line `bank shall, for the purpose of clause (e) of sub-section (1), be deemed to be unable to pay its debts:--`
  line
  line `(i) if, on the basis of the returns, statements or information furnished to the Reserve Bank under`
  line `or in pursuance of the provisions of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949), the Reserve`
  line `Bank is of opinion that the co-operative bank is unable to pay its debts; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the co-operative bank has refused to meet any lawful demand made at any of its offices or`
  line `branches within two working days, if such demand is made at a place where there is an office, branch`
  line `or agency of the Reserve Bank, or within five working days if such demand is made elsewhere and, in`
  line `either case, the Reserve Bank Certifies in writing that the co-operative bank is unable to pay its`
  line debts.]
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32185)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 19
  title `Intimation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32185&sectionno=14&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Corporation has registered any ^1[ ^2[banking`
  line `company, Regional Rural Bank] or co-operative bank] as an insured bank, it shall, within thirty days of its`
  line `registration, send an intimation in writing to the ^1[^2[banking company, Regional Rural Bank] or`
  line `co-operative bank] that it has been registered as an insured bank.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such intimation shall indicate the manner in which the premium payable by the bank under`
  line `section 15 may be calculated.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 8, for "banking company" (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1976, s. 33, for "banking company" (w.e.f. 26-9-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32186)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 20
  title Premium.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32186&sectionno=15&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every insured bank shall, so long as it continues to be registered, be liable to pay`
  line `a premium to the Corporation on its deposits at such rate or rates as may ^1[with the previous approval of`
  line `the Reserve Bank, be notified by the Corporation, from time to time, to the insured banks and different`
  line `rates may be notified for different categories of insured banks:]`
  line
  line `Provided that the premium payable by any insured bank for any period shall not exceed fifteen paisa`
  line `per annum for every hundred rupees of the total amount of the deposits in that bank at the end of that`
  line `period or, where its registration has been cancelled during that period, on the date of its cancellation:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that the Corporation may, having regard to its financial position and to the interests`
  line `of the banking system of the country as a whole, and with previous approval of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India, from time to time, raise the aforesaid limit of fifteen paisa per annum for every hundred rupees of`
  line `the total amount of the deposits in that bank:`
  line
  line `Provided also that] where the registration of any insured bank is cancelled under section 13 ^3[or`
  line `under section 13C] such cancellation shall not affect the liability of that bank for payment of premium for`
  line `the period before such cancellation and of any interest due under the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The premium shall be payable for such periods, at such times and in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) If an insured bank makes any default in payment of any amount of premium, it shall, for the`
  line `period of such default, be liable to pay to the Corporation interest on such amount at such rate ^4[not`
  line `exceeding eight per cent. over and above the bank rate as may be prescribed].`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 30 of 2021, s. 3, for “Provided further that” (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 9 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8, for not exceeding eight per cent. per annum as may be prescribed (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (32187)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 21
  title `Cancellation of registration of an insured bank for non-payment of premium.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32187&sectionno=15A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Cancellation of registration of an insured bank for non-payment of premium.--(1) The`
  line `Corporation may cancel the registration of an insured bank if it fails to pay the premium for three`
  line `consecutive periods:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such registration shall be cancelled except after giving to the concerned bank one`
  line `month's notice in writing calling upon that bank to pay the amount in default.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation may restore the registration of a bank whose registration has been cancelled`
  line `under sub-section (1), if the concerned bank requests the Corporation to restore the registration and pays`
  line `all the amounts due by way of premia from the date of default till the date of payment together with`
  line `interest due thereon on the date of payment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Corporation shall not restore the registration unless it is satisfied, on an inspection`
  line `of the concerned bank or otherwise, that it is eligible to be registered as an insured bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32188)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 22
  title `Liability of Corporation in respect of insured deposits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32188&sectionno=16&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an order for the winding up`
  line `or liquidation of an insured bank is made, the Corporation shall, subject to the other provisions of this`
  line `Act, be liable to pay to every depositor of that bank in accordance with the provisions of section 17 an`
  line `amount equal to the amount due to him in respect of his deposit in that bank at the time when such order`
  line `is made:`
  line
  line `Provided that the liability of the corporation in respect of an insured bank referred to in clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b)`
  line `^1[of sub-section (1) of section 13] ^2[or clause (a) or clause (b) of section 13C] shall be limited`
  line `to the deposits as on the date of the cancellation of the registration:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the total amount payable by the Corporation to any one depositer in respect of`
  line `his deposit in that bank in the same capacity and in the same right shall not exceed one thousand and five`
  line `hundred rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Corporation may, from time to time, having regard to its financial position`
  line `and to the interests of the banking system of the country as a whole, raise, with the previous approval of`
  line `the Central Government, the aforesaid limit of one thousand and five hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in respect of an insured bank a scheme of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction`
  line `or amalgamation has been sanctioned by any competent authority and the said scheme provides for each`
  line `depositor being paid or credited with, on the date on which the scheme comes into force, an amount`
  line `which is less than the original amount and also the specified amount, the Corporation shall be liable to`
  line `pay every such depositor in accordance with, the provisions of section 18 an amount equivalent to the`
  line `difference between the amount so paid or credited and the original amount, or the difference between the`
  line `amount so paid or credited and the specified amount, whichever is less:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such scheme also provides that any payment made to a depositor before the`
  line `coming into force of the scheme shall be reckoned towards the payment due to him under that scheme,`
  line `then the scheme shall be deemed to have provided for that payment being made on the date of its coming`
  line `into force.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, the amount of a deposit shall be determined after deducting`
  line `therefrom any ascertained sum of money which the insured banks may be legally entitled to claim by way`
  line `of set off against the depositor in the same capacity and in the same right.`
  line
  line `(4) In this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "original amount" in relation to a depositor means the total amount due by the insured bank`
  line `immediately before the date of coming into force of the scheme of compromise or arrangement or, as`
  line `the case may be, of reconstruction or amalgamation to the depositor in respect of his deposit in the`
  line `bank in the same capacity and in the same right:`
  line
  line `Provided that where under the proviso to sub-section (2), the scheme is deemed to have provided`
  line `for any payment being made on the date of its coming into force the amount of such payment shall be`
  line `included in calculating the original amount;`
  line
  line `(b) "specified amount" means one thousand and five hundred rupees, or, as the case may be, the`
  line `amount fixed by the Corporation under the third proviso to sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 62, for "of section 13" (w.e.f. 19-7-1969).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32189)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 23
  title `Manner of payment by Corporation in case of winding up of insured banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32189&sectionno=17&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an`
  line `insured bank has been ordered to be wound up or to be taken into liquidation and a liquidator, by`
  line `whatever name called, has been appointed in respect thereof, the liquidator shall, with the lest possible`
  line `delay and in any case not later than three months from the date of his assuming charge of office, furnish`
  line `to the Corporation a list in such form and manner as may be specified by the Corporation showing`
  line `separately the deposits in respect of each depositor and the amounts of set off referred to in`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 16.`
  line
  line `(2) Before the expiry of two months from the receipt of such list from the liquidator the Corporation`
  line `shall pay ^1[the amount payable under section 16 in respect of the deposit of each depositor--`
  line
  line `(a) directly to the depositor, or`
  line
  line `(b) to the depositor through such agency as the Corporation may determine, or`
  line
  line `(c) to the liquidator.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Where the Corporation pays under sub-section (2), any amount in respect of the deposit of a`
  line `depositor to the liquidator, the liquidator shall pay or cause to be paid that amount to the depositor and`
  line `any expenses incurred by the liquidator in making such payment shall be treated as expenses incurred in`
  line `the winding up of the insured bank.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32190)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 24
  title `Manner of payment by corporation in case of scheme of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction or amalgamation in respect of an insured bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32190&sectionno=18&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a scheme of`
  line `amalgamation of any insured bank with any other banking institution (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `transferee bank) or a scheme of compromise or arrangement or of reconstruction in respect of such bank`
  line `has been sanctioned and the Corporation has become liable to pay to depositors of the insured bank under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 16, the transferee bank where the scheme is of amalgamation and the insured`
  line `bank in any other case shall, with the least possible delay and in any case not later than three months from`
  line `the date on which such scheme takes effect, furnish to the Corporation a list in such form and manner as`
  line `may be specified by the Corporation and certified to be correct by the chief executive officer of the`
  line `transferee bank or, as the case may be, of the insured bank showing separately deposits in respect of each`
  line `depositor and the amounts of set off referred to in sub-section (3) of section 16 and also the amounts paid`
  line `or credited or deemed to have been paid under the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) Before the expiry of two months from the receipt of such list, the Corporation shall pay the`
  line `amount payable under section 16 either directly to the depositor or to the transferee bank or the insured`
  line `bank for being credited in his account.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (72860)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 25
  title `Liability of Corporation to make interim payment to depositors of insured bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2021, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=72860&sectionno=18A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Liability of Corporation to make interim payment to depositors of insured bank.—(1)`
  line `Where, in respect of an insured bank, —`
  line
  line `(i) any direction is issued or any prohibition or order or scheme is made under any of the`
  line `provisions of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949); and`
  line
  line `(ii) such direction, prohibition, order or scheme provides for restrictions on depositors of such`
  line `bank from accessing their deposits,`
  line
  line `then, without prejudice to the provisions of sections 16 to 18, the Corporation shall, on the date on which`
  line `such direction, prohibition, order or scheme takes effect, become liable to pay to every such depositor an`
  line `amount equivalent to the amount payable by the Corporation to the depositor under section 16.`
  line
  line `(2) A list showing the outstanding deposits of each depositor of the insured bank, as on the date`
  line `on which the direction, prohibition, order or scheme referred to in sub-section (1) takes effect, shall`
  line `be furnished by such insured bank within forty-five days of such date of effect, in such form and`
  line `manner as may be specified by the Corporation and certified to be correct by the chief executive`
  line `officer of the insured bank.`
  line
  line `(3) The Corporation shall, within thirty days of the date of receipt of the list under`
  line `sub-section (2), verify, through an online platform, to the extent possible, or in accordance with such`
  line `procedure, as may be prescribed, the genuineness and authenticity of the claims made therein, and`
  line `ascertain the willingness of each depositor to receive the amount due to him out of his deposit in the`
  line `insured bank.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (7), the Corporation shall, before the expiry of fifteen`
  line `days from the date of completion of the verification under sub-section (3), pay to the depositors who`
  line `have affirmed their willingness thereunder, the amount payable under sub-section (1) either directly,`
  line `or get it credited in the account of the depositors through the insured bank:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total period of time between the date when the Corporation becomes liable to pay to`
  line `the depositor and the date of payment to the depositor shall not, subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (7), exceed ninety days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any amount paid by the insured bank to the depositor during the period between`
  line `the date on which the direction, prohibition, order or scheme referred to in sub-section (1) takes effect and`
  line `the date of payment to the depositor, shall be appropriately reckoned by the insured bank before crediting`
  line `such amount in depositor's account.`
  line
  line `(5) Any amount paid by the Corporation under sub-section (4) in respect of a deposit shall, to the`
  line `extent of the amount so paid, discharge the insured bank from its liability to the depositor in respect of`
  line `that deposit, but the insured bank shall become liable to the Corporation in respect of the amount paid by`
  line `the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(6) Where, in respect of an insured bank, —`
  line
  line `(i) any direction, prohibition, order or scheme under any of the provisions of the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) providing for suspension of business of the insured bank is already`
  line `in force as on the date of commencement of the Deposit Insurance and Credit Guarantee Corporation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2021; and`
  line
  line `(ii) such direction, prohibition, order or scheme provides for restrictions on the amounts to be`
  line `paid by the insured bank to each of its depositors,`
  line
  line `then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Corporation`
  line `shall, on and from the date of commencement of the Deposit Insurance and Credit Guarantee Corporation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2021, become liable to pay to each depositor of such insured bank, an amount`
  line `equivalent to the amount payable by the Corporation to the depositor under sub-section (1) of section 16,`
  line `and the time limit specified in sub-sections (2) to (4) herein for such payment shall be computed from that`
  line date.
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) to (6), in cases where, —`
  line
  line `(a) the Reserve Bank finds it expedient in the interest of finalising a scheme of amalgamation of`
  line `the insured bank with other banking institution or a scheme of compromise or arrangement or of`
  line `reconstruction in respect of such insured bank, and communicates to the Corporation accordingly, the`
  line `date on which the Corporation shall become liable to pay every depositor of such insured bank may`
  line `further be extended by a period not exceeding ninety days;`
  line
  line `(b) the restrictions on payment to depositors are removed by the Reserve Bank at any time before`
  line `payment to depositors by the Corporation under sub-section (4), and the insured bank or the`
  line `transferee bank is in a position to make payments to its depositors on demand without any`
  line `restrictions, the Corporation shall not be liable to make payment to the depositors of such insured`
  line bank.
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32191)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 26
  title `Discharge of the liability of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2021, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32191&sectionno=19&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any amount paid by the Corporation under section`
  line `17 or section 18 ^1[or section 18A] in respect of a deposit shall, to the extent of the amount paid, discharge the Corporation`
  line `from its liability in respect of that deposit.`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32192)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provision for unpaid amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2021,s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32192&sectionno=20&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Where any depositor to whom any payment is to be made in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 17 or section 18 ^1[or section 18A] cannot be found or is not readily traceable,`
  line `adequate provision shall be made by the Corporation for such payment and the amount of such provision`
  line `shall be accounted for separately in its books.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (32193)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 28
  title `Repayment of the amount to corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 30 of 2021. s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-9-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32193&sectionno=21&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any amount has been paid under`
  line `section 17 or section 18 ^1[or section 18A] or any provision therefore has been made under section 20, the Corporation shall furnish to the liquidator or the insured bank or to the transferee bank, as the case may be, information as`
  line `regards the amount so paid or provided for.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the information under sub-section (1), notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(a) the liquidator shall, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, repay to the`
  line `Corporation out of the amount, if any, payable by him in respect of any deposit such sum or sums as`
  line `make up the amount paid or provided for by the Corporation in respect of that deposit;`
  line
  line `(b) the insured bank or as the case may be, the transferee bank shall, within such time and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed, repay to the Corporation out of the amount, if any, to be paid or`
  line `credited in respect of any deposit after the date of the coming into force of the scheme referred to in`
  line `section 18, such sum or sums as make up the amount paid or provided for by the Corporation in`
  line `respect of that deposit.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (32194)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 29
  title `Guaranteeing of credit facilities and indemnifying credit institutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32194&sectionno=21A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Guaranteeing of credit facilities and indemnifying credit institutions.--(1) The Corporation`
  line `may guarantee credit facilities given by any credit institution and may also indemnify credit institutions in`
  line `respect of credit facilities granted by them.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, for the purpose of guaranteeing credit facilities granted by credit institutions or`
  line `indemnifying credit institutions, frame one or more schemes in such form and in such manner and`
  line `containing such provisions as the Board may, from time to time, deem fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may levy, on every credit institution availing itself of the guarantees or indemnities`
  line `provided by the Corporation, a fee at such rate or rates as may, with the previous approval of the Reserve`
  line `Bank, be notified by the Corporation to the credit institution from time to time and different rates may be`
  line `notified for different categories of credit institutions, for different types of credit facilities, for different`
  line `areas where the credit facilities are utilised, or for different categories of beneficiaries of the credit`
  line facilities.
  line
  line `Explanation.--"Credit facility" means any financial assistance, including a loan or advance, cash`
  line `credit, overdraft, bills purchased or discounted, a term of instalment credit and any guarantee other than a`
  line `performance guarantee, granted or issued in India by a credit institution at any of its offices in India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_b:
  sectionId (32195)
  sectionNo 21B
  orderNo 30
  title `Corporation to act as agent of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32195&sectionno=21B&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_21_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[21B. Corporation to act as agent of Central Government.--The Corporation may act as agent for`
  line `the Central Government,--`
  line
  line `(i) in guaranteeing the due performance by any small-scale industrial concern or other institution`
  line `or undertaking or categories of institutions or undertakings approved by the Central Government in`
  line `this behalf, of its, or their, obligations to any credit institution in respect of loans and advances made`
  line `or other credit facilities provided to it, or them, by such credit institution, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in making, as such agent, of payments in connection with such guarantee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (32196)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 31
  title `Funds of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for section 22 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32196&sectionno=22&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Funds of Corporation.--The Corporation shall maintain three funds, to be called, respectively,`
  line `the Deposit Insurance Fund, the Credit Guarantee Fund and the General Fund.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (32197)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 32
  title `Deposit Insurance Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32197&sectionno=23&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) To the Deposit Insurance Fund shall be credited,--`
  line
  line `(a) all amounts received by the Corporation as premium;`
  line
  line `(b) all amount received by the Corporation under section 21;`
  line
  line `(c) the amount advanced by the Reserve Bank under section 26;`
  line
  line `(d) all amounts transferred to that Fund from the General Fund ^1[or the Credit Guarantee Fund]`
  line `under section 27; and`
  line
  line `(e) all income arising from the investments made out of that Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The said Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) to make payments in respect of insured deposits;`
  line
  line `(b) to meet liability in respect of an advance taken under section 26, ^2***`
  line
  line `(c) to meet liability in respect of the amounts referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1)`
  line ^3[;and]
  line
  line `^1[(d) to meet the whole or any part of the liability on account of the depreciation in assets,`
  line `contributions to staff superannuation and other funds or other expenses incurred or to be incurred by`
  line `the Corporation, as may be decided by the Board.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. The word “and” omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Added by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (32198)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 33
  title `Credit Guarantee Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32198&sectionno=23A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Credit Guarantee Fund.--(1) To the Credit Guarantee Fund shall be credited,--`
  line
  line `(a) all amounts in the Reserve for unexpired Guarantee Risks maintained by the Credit Guarantee`
  line `Corporation of India Limited, a company formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), and having its registered office at Bombay;`
  line
  line `(b) all amounts received by the Corporation as fees for guarantees and indemnities taken over or`
  line `given by it;`
  line
  line `(c) all amounts received by the Corporation in respect of guarantees and indemnities taken over`
  line `or given by it;`
  line
  line `(d) all amounts transferred to that Fund from the Deposit Insurance Fund or the General Fund`
  line `under section 27; and`
  line
  line `(e) all income arising from the investments made out of that Fund.`
  line
  line `(2) The said Fund shall be applied--`
  line
  line `(a) to make payments in respect of guarantees and indemnities taken over or issued by the`
  line Corporation;
  line
  line `(b) to meet any liability in respect of the amount referred to in clause (d) of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(c) to meet the whole or any part of the liability on account of depreciation in assets, contributions`
  line `to staff superannuation and other funds, or other expenses incurred or to be incurred by the`
  line `Corporation, as may be decided by the Board;]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (32199)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 34
  title `General Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32199&sectionno=24&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `All receipts of the Corporation other than those referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 23 ^1[or in sub-section (1) of section 23A] shall be credited to the General Fund and all payments`
  line `by the Corporation other than those referred to in sub-section (2)`
  line `^1[of section 23, or, as the case may be,`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 23A] shall be made out of that Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (32200)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 35
  title Investment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32200&sectionno=25&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `All moneys belonging to the Deposit Insurance Fund ^1[or the Credit Guarantee`
  line `Fund] or the General Fund which may not for the time being be required by the Corporation shall be`
  line `invested in promissory notes, stock or securities of the Central Government and all other moneys shall be`
  line `deposited with the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (32201)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 36
  title `Amount in one fund may be transferred to the other fund or may be utilised for other purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32201&sectionno=25A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Amounts in one Fund may be transferred to the other Fund or may be utilised for other`
  line `purposes.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Board may--`
  line
  line `(a) transfer any amount from the Deposit Insurance Fund to the Credit Guarantee Fund or from`
  line `the Credit Guarantee fund to the Deposit Insurance Fund, or`
  line
  line `(b) utilise any money standing to the credit of either of the said Funds, for such purposes as it`
  line `may think fit, if it is satisfied that the balance in the Fund, after such transfer or utilisation, will be`
  line `adequate to meet any probable claim on that Fund.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (32202)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 37
  title `Advances by Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32202&sectionno=26&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Reserve Bank shall, from time to time, advance to the`
  line `Corporation on a request by it such sum or sums as may be required by the Corporation for the purposes`
  line `of the Deposit Insurance Fund ^1[or the Credit Guarantee Fund]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total amount outstanding at any one time on account of such advances shall not`
  line `exceed five crores of rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of any advance under this section shall be such as may be determined by`
  line `the Reserve Bank with the approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (32203)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 38
  title `Advances from General Fund to the Deposit Insurance Fund or Credit Guarantee Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for section 27 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32203&sectionno=27&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `^1[27. Advances From General Fund to the Deposit Insurance Fund or Credit Guarantee`
  line `Fund.--If, at any time, the amount available in the Deposit Insurance Fund or the Credit Guarantee Fund`
  line `is insufficient to meet the requirements of that Fund, the Corporation may transfer, on such terms and for`
  line `such period as may be determined by the Board with the approval of the Reserve Bank, from any of the`
  line `other two Funds, referred to in section 22, such amount as may be necessary to meet the requirements of`
  line `the Deposit Insurance Fund or the Credit Guarantee Fund, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (32204)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 39
  title `Preparation of balance-sheet, etc., by corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32204&sectionno=28&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The balance-sheet and accounts of the`
  line `Corporation shall be prepared and maintained in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall cause the books and accounts of the Corporation to be balanced and closed as on`
  line `the 31st day of December ^1[or such other date in each year as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify]:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that with a view to facilitating the transition from one period of accounting to another`
  line `period of accounting under this sub-section, the Central Government may, by order published in the`
  line `Official Gazette, make such provision as it considers necessary or expedient for the balancing and closing`
  line `of, or for other matters relating to, the books or accounts in respect of the concerned years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 25, for ", each year" (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 25, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (32205)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 40
  title Audit.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32205&sectionno=29&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The affairs of the Corporation shall be audited by an auditor duly qualified to act as`
  line `an auditor under sub-section (1) of section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), who shall be`
  line `appointed by the Board with the previous approval of the Reserve Bank and shall receive such`
  line `remuneration from the Corporation as the Reserve Bank may fix.`
  line
  line `(2) The auditor shall be supplied with a copy of the annual balance-sheet of the Corporation and it`
  line `shall be his duty to examine it together with the accounts and vouchers relating thereto and he shall have a`
  line `list delivered to him of all books kept by the Corporation and shall at all reasonable times have to the`
  line `books, accounts and other documents of the Corporation and may, in relation to such accounts examine`
  line `any director of the Board or any officer or employee of the Corporation.`
  line
  line `(3) The auditor shall make a report to the Corporation upon the annual balance-sheet and accounts`
  line `and in every such report he shall state whether in his opinion the balance-sheet is a full and fair`
  line `balance-sheet containing all necessary particulars and properly drawn up so as to exhibit a true and`
  line `correct view of the state of affairs of the Corporation and in case he had called for any explanation or`
  line `information from the Board, whether it has been given and whether it is satisfactory.`
  line
  line `(4) Without prejudice to anything contained in the preceding sub-sections, the Central Government`
  line `may at any time appoint the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India to examine and report upon the`
  line `accounts of the Corporation, and any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such examination`
  line `and report shall be payable by the Corporation to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (32206)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 41
  title Income-tax.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32206&sectionno=30&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `^1[30. Income-tax--^2[(1)] Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961), the Corporation shall not be liable to pay any tax under that Act on any of its incoming`
  line `profits or gains for the accounting year during which the Corporation is established and for ^3[fourteen`
  line `accounting years following that year.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), the Corporation`
  line `shall not be liable to pay any tax under that Act on any of its income, profits or gains for the period`
  line `commencing from the first day of January, 1977, and ending with the commencement of the accounting`
  line `year during which Chapter II of the Deposit Insurance Corporation (Amendment and Miscellaneous`
  line `Provisions) Act, 1978 (21 of 1978), comes into force and for four accounting years following that years.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 1967, s. 44, for section 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line
  line `2. Section 30 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 53, for "nine accounting years" (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (32207)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 42
  title `Reserve Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32207&sectionno=31&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `After making provisions for all its liabilities and for all other matters for which`
  line `provision is necessary or expedient, including any contribution to the staff and super annuation funds, the`
  line `Corporation shall transfer the balance, if any, of its income in its General Fund to one or more reserve`
  line `funds to be utilised in such manner and for such purposes as the Corporation may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (32208)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 43
  title `Annual accounts and reports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32208&sectionno=32&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall furnish to the Reserve Bank within`
  line `three months from the date on which its accounts are balanced and closed the balance-sheet and accounts`
  line `together with the auditor's report and a report of the working of the Corporation during the year and`
  line `copies of the said balance-sheet and accounts and reports shall be furnished by the Corporation to the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall cause every auditor's report and report of the working of the`
  line `Corporation to be laid ^1[as soon as may be after they received before each House of Parliament ^2***.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 5. Subs. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 63, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
  line
  line `2. The words ", while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more`
  line `successive sessions" omitted by Act 81 of 1985, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (32209)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 44
  title `Staff of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32209&sectionno=33&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may appoint such number of officers and employees`
  line `as it considers necessary or desirable for the efficient performance of its functions and determine the`
  line `terms and conditions of their appointment and service.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the Corporation to`
  line `utilise, and for the Reserve Bank to make available, the services of such staff of the Reserve Bank on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be agreed upon between the Corporation and the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (32210)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 45
  title `Returns from insured banks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32210&sectionno=34&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in ^2[the Banking`
  line `Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)] or any other law for the time being in force the Corporation may at`
  line `any time direct an insured bank ^1[or a credit institution] to furnish to it, within such time as may be`
  line `specified by the Corporation, such statements and information relating to the deposits in that bank ^1[or the`
  line `credit facilities granted by that credit institution, as the case may be,] as the Corporation may consider`
  line `necessary or expedient to obtain for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation may, if it considers it expedient and after consulting the Reserve Bank, publish`
  line `any information obtained by it under this section in such consolidated form as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 2, for "the Banking Companies Act, 1949" (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (32211)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 46
  title `Corporation to have access to records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32211&sectionno=35&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall have free access to all such`
  line `records of an insured bank ^1[or a credit institution] perusal where of may appear to the Corporation to the`
  line `necessary for the discharge of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Corporation may require any insured bank ^1[or credit institution] to furnish to it copies of any`
  line `of the records referred to in sub-section (1) and the bank ^1[or the credit institution] shall be bound to`
  line `comply with the requisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (32212)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 47
  title `Inspection of insured banks by Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32212&sectionno=36&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation may for any of the`
  line `purposes of this Act request the Reserve Bank to cause an inspection of the books and accounts or an`
  line `investigation of the affairs of an insured bank ^1[or a credit institution] to be made and on such request the`
  line `Reserve Bank shall cause such inspection or investigation to be made by one or more of its officers ^2[or`
  line `through such other person or agency as the Reserve Bank may determine.]`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (2) and sub-section (3) of section 35 of ^3[the Banking Regulation`
  line `Act, 1949 (10 of 1949)] shall apply to an inspection or investigation under sub-section (1) as they apply to`
  line `an inspection under that section.`
  line
  line `(3) When an inspection or investigation has been made under this section, the Reserve Bank shall`
  line `furnish a copy of its report to the Corporation and ^4[neither the bank nor the credit institution, as the case`
  line `may be, inspected or investigated, nor any other bank or credit institution] shall be entitled to be furnished`
  line `with a copy of such report.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, no court, Tribunal or`
  line `other authority shall compel the production or disclosure of a report under this section or of information`
  line `or material gathered during the course of an inspection or investigation under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Banking Companies Act, 1949" (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (32213)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 48
  title `Corporation to furnish information to Reserve Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32213&sectionno=37&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Corporation shall, one a request in`
  line `writing from the Reserve Bank, furnish to it within such time as may be specified by the Reserve Bank,`
  line `such statement and information relating to the business or affairs of the Corporation or of an insured bank`
  line `as the Reserve Bank may consider necessary or expedient.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (32214)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 49
  title `Reserve Bank to furnish information to Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32214&sectionno=38&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Reserve Bank shall, on a request`
  line `in writing from the Corporation, furnish to it any report or information relating to an insured bank`
  line `^1[or a`
  line `credit institution] made or obtained by it under or in pursuance of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 or`
  line `^2[the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949).]`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "the Banking Companies Act, 1949" (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (32215)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 50
  title `Declaration of fidelity and secrecy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32215&sectionno=39&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^2[(1)] Every director, auditor, officer or other employee of`
  line `the Corporation or an employee of the Reserve Bank whose services are utilised by the Corporation under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 33 shall, before entering upon his duties, make a declaration of fidelity and`
  line `secrecy in the form set out in the First Schedule to this Act.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) The Corporation shall observe, except as otherwise required by law, the practices and usages`
  line `customary among the bankers, and, in particular, it shall not divulge any information relating to an`
  line `insured bank or its customers or a credit institution or its customers except in circumstances in which it is,`
  line `in accordance with law or practices or usages customary among bankers, necessary or appropriate for the`
  line `Corporation to divulge such information.]`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the credit information disclosed under the Credit`
  line `Information Companies (Regulation) Act, 2005.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Section 39 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 30 of 2005, s. 34 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 14-12-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (32216)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 51
  title `Indemnity of directors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32216&sectionno=40&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every director of the Board shall be indemnified by the`
  line `Corporation against all losses and expenses incurred by him in, or in relation to, the discharge of his`
  line `duties except such as are caused by his own willful act or default.`
  line
  line `(2) A director of the Board shall not be responsible for any other director or for any other officer or`
  line `other employee of the Corporation, or for any loss or expenses resulting to the Corporation from the`
  line `insufficiency or deficiency of value of or title to any property or security acquired or taken on behalf of`
  line `the Corporation or the insolvency or wrongful act of any debtor or any person under obligation to the`
  line `Corporation or anything done in good faith in the execution of the duties of his office or in relation`
  line thereto.
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (32217)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 52
  title `Defects in appointment not to invalidate acts, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32217&sectionno=41&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) No act or proceeding of the Board or`
  line `of any committee of the Corporation shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Board or committee.`
  line
  line `(2) No act done by any person acting in good faith as a director of the Board shall be deemed to be`
  line `invalid merely on the ground that he was disqualified to be a director or that there was any other defect in`
  line `his appointment.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (32218)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 53
  title `Protection of action taken under this act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by 56 of 1968, s. 13, for "or any other person authorised by the Corporation" (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32218&sectionno=42&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `No suit other legal proceeding shall lie against the`
  line `Corporation or the Reserve Bank or any director of the Board or any officer of the Corporation or the`
  line `Reserve Bank or ^1[or any other person or agency authorised by the Corporation or the Reserve Bank] to`
  line `discharge any functions under this Act for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is`
  line `in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (32219)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 54
  title `Companies Act, 1956 and insurance act, 1938 not to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32219&sectionno=43&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in the Companies Act,`
  line `1956 (1 of 1956) or the Insurance Act, 1938 (4 of 1938), shall apply to the Corporation.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (50607)
  sectionNo 43A
  orderNo 55
  title `Powers of Reserve Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 50 of 2019, s. 33 and the second Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-2019)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=50607&sectionno=43A&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_43_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[43A. Powers of Reserve Bank not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.--`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the powers exercisable`
  line `by the Reserve Bank under this Act,`
  line
  line `(a) shall not extend to an International Financial Services Centre set up under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(b) shall be exercisable by the International Financial Services Centres Authority established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4 of the International Financial Services Centres Authority Act, 2019,`
  line `in so far as regulation of financial products, financial services and financial institutions that are`
  line `permitted in the International Financial Services Centres are concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (32220)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 56
  title `Liquidation of Corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32220&sectionno=44&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Corporation shall not be placed in liquidation save by`
  line `order of the Central Government and in such manner as that Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) On the liquidation of the Corporation--`
  line
  line `(a) the outstanding assets of the Corporation in so far as they relate to the Deposit Insurance Fund`
  line `shall be distributed among the insured banks in such manner and in such proportion as may be`
  line `determined by the Central Government having regard to the amounts of premium paid by them during`
  line `any prescribed period or the deposits of the said banks as on the date of liquidation of the Corporation`
  line `or other relevant circumstances;`
  line
  line `(b) the remaining outstanding assets of the Corporation shall be transferred to the Reserve Bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (32221)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 57
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32221&sectionno=45&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `In the discharge of its functions under this`
  line `Act, the Corporation shall be guided by such directions in matters of policy involving public interest as`
  line `the Central Government may after consulting the Reserve Bank give to it in writing, and if any question`
  line `arises whether the directions relates to a matter of policy involving public interest, the decision of the`
  line `Central Government thereon shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (32222)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 58
  title `Dispute as to amount of premium.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32222&sectionno=46&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any dispute as to the amount of premium due from any`
  line `insured bank shall be decided by the Central Government and the decision of that Government shall final.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (32223)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 59
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and Schedule for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 22-01-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32223&sectionno=47&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever in any return, balance-sheet or other document or in any information`
  line `required or furnished by or under or for the purposes of any provision of this Act, willfully makes a`
  line `statement which is false in any material particular, knowing it to be false, or willfully omits to make a`
  line `material statement, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) If any person fails to produce any book, account or other document or to furnish any statement or information which, under the provisions of this Act, it is his duty to produce or furnish, he shall be liable to penalty which may extend to one lakh fifty thousand rupees in respect of each failure, and in the case of a continuing failure, with an additional penalty which may extend to seven thousand five hundred rupees for every day during which the failure continues after the first such failure.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of adjudging the penalty under sub-section (2), the Corporation shall serve notice on the person requiring it to show cause why the amount specified in the notice should not be imposed and a reasonable opportunity of being heard shall also be given to such person.`
  line
  line `(4) Any penalty imposed by the Corporation under this section shall be payable within a period of fourteen days from the date on which notice issued by the Corporation demanding payment of the sum is served on the person and in the event of failure of the person to pay the sum within such period, may be levied on an order or direction made by the principal civil court having jurisdiction in the area where the person is situated:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order or direction shall be made except on an application made to the court by the Corporation or any officer authorised by it in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(5) The court which makes an order or direction under sub-section (4) shall issue a certificate specifying the sum payable by the person and every such certificate shall be enforceable in the same manner as if it were a decree made by the court in a civil suit.`
  line
  line `(6) No complaint shall be filed against any person in any court of law in respect of any contravention or default in respect of which any penalty has been imposed by the Corporation under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(7) Where any complaint has been filed against any person in any court in respect of any contravention or default of the nature referred to in sub-section (1), then, no proceedings for the imposition of any penalty on the person shall be initiated under sub-section (2).]`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (32224)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 60
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 56 of 1968, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-7-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32224&sectionno=48&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence has been committed by a company, every person`
  line `who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company, shall be deemed to be guilty of the`
  line `offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any gross negligence on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes ^1[a co-operative society or] a firm or other`
  line `association of individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm ^1[and in relation to a co-operative`
  line `society includes any member of a committee of management or other managing body (by whatever`
  line `name called) to which the management of the affairs of the bank is entrusted].`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (32225)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 61
  title `Cognizance and trial of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1978, s. 8, for section 49 (w.e.f. 15-7-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32225&sectionno=49&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `^1[49. Cognizance and trial of offences.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no Court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under`
  line `this Act except upon a complaint, in writing, made by an officer of the Corporation, generally or specially`
  line `authorised in writing in this behalf by the Board, and no court, inferior to the Court of a Metropolitan`
  line `Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class, shall try any such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), a`
  line `Magistrate may, if he sees reason so to do, dispense with the personal attendance of the officer of the`
  line `Corporation filing the complaint, but the Magistrate may, in his discretion, at any stage of the proceeding,`
  line `direct the personal attendance of the complainant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (32226)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 62
  title Regulation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164&sectionId=32226&sectionno=50&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00020_196147_1517807321164
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, with the previous approval of the Reserve Bank, ^1[by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette,] make regulations not inconsistent with this Act to provide for all`
  line `matters for which provision is necessary or expedient for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the times and places of the meetings of the Board or of any committee constituted under this`
  line `Act and the procedure to be followed at such meetings including the quorum necessary for the`
  line `transaction of business;`
  line
  line `(b) the number of directors constituting an Executive Committee, and the functions that such`
  line `committee shall discharge;`
  line
  line `(c) the functions which any other committee may discharge under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the fees and allowances that may be paid to the members of a committee other than directors`
  line `of the Board;`
  line
  line `(e) the fees and allowances that may be paid to the directors of the Board;`
  line
  line `(f) the periods for which, the times at which and the manner in which premium may be paid by an`
  line `insured bank;`
  line
  line `(g) the interest which may be charged from an insured bank where it makes default in payment of`
  line premium;
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which and the time within which the amounts referred to in section 21 may be`
  line paid;
  line
  line `(i) the form and the manner in which the balance-sheet and the accounts of the Corporation shall`
  line `be prepared or maintained; and`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be, or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any regulation which may be made by the Board under this Act may be made by the Reserve`
  line `Bank within three months of the establishment of the Corporation; and any regulation so made may be`
  line `altered or rescinded by the Board in the exercise of its powers under this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) Every regulation shall, as soon as may be after it is made under this Act by the Board, be`
  line `forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall cause a copy of the same to be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the regulation, or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 66 of 1988, s. 26 (w.e.f. 30-12-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 1984, s. 64 (w.e.f. 15-2-1984).`
